<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qt3d-render-rendersurfaceselector.xml">RenderSurfaceSelector</db:link> can be used to select the surface, where Qt3D renders the content. The surface can either be window surface or offscreen surface. The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qt3d-render-rendersurfaceselector.xml#externalRenderTargetSize-prop">externalRenderTargetSize</db:link> is used to specify the actual size of the render target when offscreen surface is used.</db:para>
<db:para>When DPI scaling is used by the system, the logical surface size, which is used by mouse events, and the actual 'physical' size of the surface can differ. The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qt3d-render-rendersurfaceselector.xml#surfacePixelRatio-prop">surfacePixelRatio</db:link> is the factor to convert the logical size to the physical size.</db:para>
</db:section>
